Hppc does this:
      for (IntCursor cursor : IntArrayList.from(3, 6, 5)) {
            System.out.println(cursor.value);
      }
and here we get the IntCursor when calling next on the Iterator<IntCursor>, so the IntCursor here is the equivalent to our EdgeIteratorState (the proxy object that gives access to the index and value of an int array for example).

